  "prompt": "Does my H1B visa transfer impact my spouse's H4 visa?",
  "response": "When you transfer your H1B visa to a new employer, your spouse's H4 visa status is typically not directly impacted. However, your spouse will usually need to update their visa documentation to reflect your new employment. The specific steps include:\n\n1. Your H4 spouse can remain in the same status\n2. They will need a new I-94 form reflecting the updated employment\n3. If traveling internationally, they may need a new H4 visa stamp\n4. Their work authorization (if previously approved for EAD) generally remains valid\n\nFor the most accurate and current guidance, I recommend consulting:\n- Your new employer's immigration lawyer\n- USCIS official website\n- An immigration attorney who can review your specific situation\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
